a long time and can extend battery life.\",DOC.lbl.stopChargeTip1=\"1. After the switch is turned on, the device battery icon will not show the charging status when the power is connected.\",DOC.lbl.stopChargeTip2=\"2. It is recommended not to permanently turn on the switch, but to turn it off periodically to allow the battery to charge and discharge naturally. Do not leave the battery fully charged or undercharged for a long time.\",DOC.lbl.stopChargeTip3=\"If the battery is completely depleted for a long time, the battery may fall into a deep discharge state, resulting in the inability to recharge. On the contrary, if the battery is fully charged for a long time, it may Part of the battery capacity is lost, thus shortening the battery life. It is recommended to charge and discharge the battery once a month. \",DOC.lbl.stopCharge=\"Stop charging\",DOC.lbl.internet=\"Internet\",DOC.lbl.agent=\"Agent\",DOC.lbl.controller=\"Controller\",DOC.lbl.sta=\"STA\",DOC.lbl.chartInfo=\"Chart information\",DOC.lbl.batteryCap=\"Battery Power Curve\",DOC.lbl.esimSdkVersion=\"ESIM SDK version\",DOC.lbl.linkTypeWifi=\"Wireless connection\",DOC.lbl.linkTypeWrid=\"Wired connection\",DOC.lbl.anonymousHost=\"Anonymous Host\",DOC.lbl.dataWireClose=\"Wired data is not connected\",DOC.lbl.dataMobileClose=\"Mobile data is not connected\",DOC.lbl.ussdContent=\"Contents\",PROMPT.tips.reply=\"Reply\",DOC.lbl.ussdReply=\"Reply to\",DOC.btn.ussdAirtime=\"Check Airtime Balance\",DOC.btn.ussdData=\"Check Data Balance\",DOC.btn.ussdNumber=\"Check My Number\",CHECK.tip.ipIsInPool=\"{0} is not within the DHCP address pool range. Do you want to continue saving?\",DOC.lbl.paramsNotChange=\"Parameters not modified\",DOC.lbl.smartChangeCard=\"Smart card change switch\",DOC.lbl.clearUsed=\"After modifying the start date of the billing cycle, the traffic used in the current month will be cleared. Do you want to continue?\",DOC.lbl.yoctoLevel=\"YOCTO Level\",DOC.lbl.reportInterval=\"Reporting Interval\",DOC