uage=\"en\",DOC.lbl.lockTh=\"Lock Physical Cell\",DOC.lbl.lockSpecific=\"Lock Specific Physical Cell\",DOC.lbl.unlock=\"Unlock\",DOC.lbl.lockedStatus3g=\"3G Locked Cell\",DOC.lbl.lockedStatus4g=\"4G Locked Cell\",DOC.lbl.lockedStatus5g=\"5G Locked Cell\",DOC.lbl.freqPoint=\"EARFCN\",DOC.lbl.phyCellId=\"Physical Cell ID\",DOC.lbl.btnSave=\"Apply\",DOC.lbl.readFail=\"Read failed.\",DOC.lbl.advancedOptions=\"Advanced Options\",DOC.lbl.accept=\"Whitelist\",DOC.lbl.all=\"All\",DOC.lbl.autoDial=\"Automatic dialing\",DOC.lbl.cycle=\"Infinite\",DOC.lbl.dataRoamingEnable=\"Enable\",DOC.lbl.dataRoamingDisable=\"Disable\",DOC.lbl.dataRoamingStart=\"Open\",DOC.lbl.dataRoamingStop=\"Close\",DOC.lbl.ddns=\"DDNS\",DOC.lbl.defaultText=\"Default\",DOC.lbl.dns=\"DNS\",DOC.lbl.SCANEnable=\"SCAN\",DOC.lbl.ecgiLockEnable=\"PCI Lock\",DOC.lbl.ecgiLockExample=\"Example: 503\",DOC.lbl.ecgiLockId=\"PCI Lock ID\",DOC.lbl.ecgiLockIdList=\"PCI Lock ID List\",DOC.lbl.ecgiWarning=\"Warning: You are out of cell range and the device is locked!\",DOC.lbl.example=\"Example\",DOC.lbl.fileSize=\"File Size\",DOC.lbl.fotaUrl=\"FOTA URL\",DOC.lbl.ifDefault=\"(If the value is empty, default value is WAN Interface)\",DOC.lbl.ifName=\"Interface\",DOC.lbl.ipv4FilterRule=\"Default Filter Rules\",DOC.lbl.ipv6FilterRule=\"IPv6 default filter rules\",DOC.lbl.loadAvg=\"Average Load\",DOC.lbl.prompt=\"Prompt\",DOC.lbl.lockedStatus=\"Locked Status\",DOC.lbl.lockFreqPointTipRange=\"Range: 1 ~ 16777215\",DOC.lbl.lockFreqPointTipRange5g=\"Rango: 1 ~ 2016666\",DOC.lbl.lockPhyCellIdTipRange=\"Range: 0 ~ 503\",DOC.lbl.lockPhyCellIdTipRange5g=\"Range: 0 ~ 1007\",DOC.lbl.getCurrent=\"Get\",DOC.lbl.memory=\"Memory\",DOC.lbl.memoryCache=\"Memory Cache\",DOC.lbl.memoryFree=\"Memory Free\",DOC.lbl.memoryTotal=\"Memory Total\",DOC.lbl.netMode=\"Network Mode\",DOC.lbl.netSetting=\"Network Configuration\",DOC.lbl.flightMode=\"Flight Mode\",DOC.lbl.pinCode=\"PIN Code\",DOC.lbl.simChange=\"SIM Switch\",DOC.lbl.notChange=\"The SIM card type has not changed\",DOC.lbl.qrcord=\"Device Information\",DOC.lbl.qrcode=\"QR code\",DOC.lbl.qrcodeNoEid=\"Unrecognized EID\",DOC.lbl.qrcodeNoIoti=\"Unrecognized IOTI\",DOC.lbl.resetESIM=\"Unregister and reset eSIM\",DOC.lbl.downESIM=\"Download to activate eSIM\",DOC.lbl.esimState=\"eSIM active status\",DOC.lbl.esimStateYes=\"Activated\",DOC.lbl.esimStateNo=\"Unactivated\",DOC.lbl.esimEmpty=\"eSIM card not attached or eSIM damaged\",DOC.lbl.download=\"Download\",DOC.lbl.officialQrcord=\"Official Accounts\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle=\"eSIM card opening process\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle0=\"Please prepare the following environment: 1 PC, 1 network cable, 1 mobile phone that can use the Internet\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle11=\"Operate the phone:\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle1=\"1.1. Follow the WeChat official account of 'My eSIM' by operating the mobile phone, and activate eSIM according to the guidelines of the WeChat official account. In the process of opening the eSIM service, you need to scan the 'device information' QR code at the bottom of the CPE as prompted.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle2=\"1.2. After the WeChat official account completes the binding of the eSIM card to the user, it is necessary to wait for the SMS result returned by the eSIM platform.If the SMS feedback is successful, continue to follow the instructions on the 'My eSIM' WeChat official account; if the result is unsuccessful, contact your sales consultant for help.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle3=\"1.3. After completing the operation of the 'My eSIM' WeChat official account, turn on the mobile hotspot, the password is set by you, or set to blank.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle22=\"Operation CPE:\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle4=\"2.1. Without inserting the physical SIM card, turn on the CPE, connect the PC and the CPE through the network cable, and wait for the CPE terminal signal indicator to turn on.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle5=\"2.2. Log in to the WEB management page 192.168.0.1 from the PC side browser, the login name and password are both admin by default.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle6=\"2.3. Enter the 'Network Function'-'SIM Function'-'SIM Card Switching' page, and switch the card to the 'Built-in SIM Card' state.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle7=\"2.4. Enter the 'Network Function'-'Mobile Network Configuration'-'WAN Mode' page, select the '2.4 GHz Wi-Fi' or '5 GHz Wi-Fi' network mode according to your mobile phone hotspot (usually, the mobile phone hotspot is It is 2.4 GHz AP).Fill in the hotspot name (SSID) and password of the mobile phone.If the mobile hotspot has no password, change the 'Authentication Type' to ‘Open System’; or if the mobile hotspot has a password, select 'WPA/WPA2-PSK' and click Connect to connect the CPE terminal to the mobile hotspot.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle8=\"2.5. Enter the 'eSIM management' page and click on 'download and activate' to complete the eSIM activation operation.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle9=\"2.6. Enter the 'Network Function'-'Mobile Network Configuration'-'WAN Mode' page, and switch back to the 'Mobile Network Mode'.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle10=\"2.7. Enter the 'System Management'-'Restart Device' page, and click OK in the pop-up restart confirmation box. After the CPE restarts, you can use your eSIM card normally.\",DOC.lbl.esimTitle1_1='Search for the \"CTWing 翼品\" applet in WeChat, log in to the IoT enablement kit number you ordered, enter the business-enterprise express application, and add devices to complete device binding and real-name authentication according to the operating instructions operate. When you see the device information on the business-enterprise express application page, and the status is inactive, it means that the device has been added. ',DOC.lbl.esimTitle2_1=\"1. Plug the CPE power supply, and connect the device to the PC through a network cable, or use a computer to connect to the CPE device Wi-Fi network (the default account and password can be viewed at the bottom of the device, and set to automatically obtain an IP address ). \",DOC.lbl.esimTitle2_2=\"2. Log in to the WEB management page 192.168.0.1 in the PC browser, the login name and password are both admin by default. \",DOC.lbl.esimTitle2_3='3. Enter the \"Network Function\"-\"SIM Function\"-\"SIM Card Switching\" page, and switch the card to the \"Built-in SIM Card\" state. ',DOC.lbl.esimTitle2_4='4. Enter \"Network Function\"-\"Mobile Network Configuration\"-\"WAN Mode\", and connect to a Wi-Fi network that can access the Internet, such as mobile hotspots and home broadband. Choose the \"2.4 GHz Wi-Fi\" or \"5 GHz Wi-Fi\" network mode according to your on-site environment (usually, the mobile phone hotspot is 2.4 GHz AP). Fill in the name (SSID) and password of the Wi-Fi/mobile hotspot. Note: If the mobile hotspot has no password, change the \"Authentication Type\" to \"Open System\" or the mobile hotspot has a password, select \"WPA/WPA2-PSK\" and click Connect to connect the CPE terminal to the mobile hotspot. ',DOC.lbl.esimTitle2_5='5. Enter the \"eSIM Management\" page and click \"Download and activate\" to complete the eSIM activation operation. ',DOC.lbl.esimTitle2_6='6. Enter the \"Network Function\"-\"Mobile Network Configuration\"-\"WAN Mode\" page, and switch back to \"Mobile Network Mode\". ',DOC.lbl.esimTitle2_7='7. Enter the applet to check the device status. If it is offline, you can enter the \"System Management\"-\"Restart Device\" page, and click OK in the pop-up restart confirmation box. After the CPE restarts, you can Use your eSIM card normally. ',DOC.lbl.resetESIMTips1=\"This operation will cancel the current eSIM card number and reset it to the factory state. If you are not an O&M personnel, please do not click Confirm. Are you sure to continue operation?\",DOC.lbl.resetESIMTips2=\"Please reconfirm whether to log out and reset the eSIM card\",DOC.lbl.uploadEsim=\"It takes about 1 minute to download the data. Please do not refresh the interface or turn off the power.\",DOC.lbl.pinOper=\"PIN Operation\",DOC.lbl.pinOper1=\"Enable PIN\",DOC.lbl.pinOper2=\"Disable PIN\",DOC.lbl.pin