port DDNS, you need to register on the corresponding DDNS server before configuration, and the DDNS service provider will provide you with a user name and password\",TAB.advance.ddnsUsernameInfo=\"Enter your username registered on the DDNS server.\",TAB.advance.ddnsPasswordInfo=\"Enter the password you registered on the DDNS server.\",TAB.advance.ddnsDomainInfo=\"Enter the domain name you applied for at the website domain name management agency.\",TAB.voice.voiceAdvanced=\"Voice Advanced Settings\",TAB.voice.voiceBasic=\"Voice Basic Settings\",TAB.voice.VoLTESettings=\"VoLTE Settings\",TAB.voice.voipSettings=\"VoIP Settings\",TAB.voice.voipAdvancedSettings=\"VoIP Advanced Settings\",TAB.voice.voipCallCipher=\"Special Key Code Settings\",TAB.voice.voiceType=\"Voice Type\",TAB.voice.voiceAutoSw=\"Automatically Switch\",TAB.voice.digitMapSwitch=\"Digit Map Switch\",TAB.voice.digitMapRule=\"Digit Map Rules\",TAB.voice.dialDelay=\"Dial Delay\",TAB.voice.polaritySw=\"Line Reversal\",TAB.voice.hotLine=\"Hotline\",TAB.voice.slicTxGain=\"Audio TX Gain\",TAB.voice.slicRxGain=\"Audio RX Gain\",TAB.voice.voiceTypeText=\"Set the voice type of the current device\",TAB.voice.voiceAutoSwText=\"When enabled, when voice VoIP configuration is unavailable, it will automatically switch to VoLTE.\",TAB.voice.digitMapSwitchText=\"Whether to enable Digit Map function\",TAB.voice.digitMapRuleText=\"Dial plan, used to detect and report terminal dialing events\",TAB.voice.dialDelayText=\"That is, the time to dial out the number after waiting for a certain time after off-hook dialing, unit (seconds)\",TAB.voice.polaritySwText=\"After the outgoing call, the charging signal is generated by reversing the polarity of the slic voltage\",TAB.voice.hotLineText=\"The current hotline call is automatically called out when there is no action beyond the specified time (dial delay) after the pick-up\",TAB.voice.slicTxGainText=\"Defined as a total of 5 gears, and the default is the middle gear\",TAB.voice.slicRxGainText=\"Defined as a total of 5 gears, and the default is the middle gear\",fourgInfohtml.helper.title2=\"Network Parameter\",fourgInfohtml.helper.item2=\"<li>RSRP: Reference Signal Receiving Power</li><li>RSSI: Received Signal Strength Indication</li><li>RSRQ: Reference Signal Receiving Quality</li><li>SINR: Signal to Interference plus Noise Ratio</li><li>PCI: Physical Cell Identifier</li><li>eNodeB/gNodeB ID: 4G/5G NodeB ID</li><li>CQI: Channel Quality Indicator </li><li>MCS: Modulation and Coding Scheme</li><li>Band: The Bandwidth of Mobile Network</li><li>ECGI: E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier</li>\",wanInfohtml.helper.title1=\"APN\",wanInfohtml.helper.item1=\"<li>APN refers to a network access configuration, which is a parameter that must be set when the MiFi device is online. It determines how the MiFi connects to the mobile network.</li>\",wanInfohtml.helper.title2=\"Access Parameter\",wanInfohtml.helper.item2=\"<li>IP:&nbsp;&nbsp;An IP address is a numerical label assigned to each device connected to a computer network that uses the Internet Protocol for communication.</li>\",wifiInfohtml.helper.title3=\"Enable Wi-Fi\",wifiInfohtml.helper.item3=\"Show Wi-Fi is opened or closed\",wifiInfohtml.helper.title4=\"SSID\",wifiInfohtml.helper.item4=\"The name of WLAN\",wifiInfohtml.helper.title5=\"MAC Address\",wifiInfohtml.helper.item5=\"A MAC address of a device is a unique identifier assigned to a network interface controller (NIC)\",wifiInfohtml.helper.title6=\"SSID Broadcast\",wifiInfohtml.helper.item6=\"It is convenient for wireless devices (mobile phones, tablets, notebooks, desktop computers with wireless network cards) to search for wireless signals from the router\",wifiInfohtml.helper.title7=\"Channel\",wifiInfohtml.helper.item7=\"In order to multiplex communication, the available frequency segments are divided into multiple small segments, and different devices are allowed to use only specific frequency bands\",lanInfohtml.helper.title1=\"LAN Network\",lanInfohtml.helper.item1=\"LAN Network is the Server gate of the LAN.\";lanInfohtml.helper.title2=\"Interface\",lanInfohtml.helper.item2=\"Interface is the network intereface of this LAN.\",lanInfohtml.helper.title3=\"Begin/End IP\",lanInfohtml.helper.item3=\"Begin/End IP are the range of the LAN network.\",DOC.vpn.tunnelName=\"Tunnel Name\",networkconfightml.form1.ipAddres=\"IP Address Reservation\",networkconfightml.form1.td5=\"Hours\",networkconfightml.form1.th1=\"LAN IP:\",networkconfightml.form1.th2=\"Subnet Mask:\",networkconfightml.form1.th3=\"DHCP Server:\",networkconfightml.form1.th4=\"IP Address Pool:\",networkconfightml.form1.th5=\"Lease Time:\",networkconfightml.form1.th6=\"Primary DNS:\",networkconfightml.form1.th7=\"Secondary DNS:\",networkconfightml.form1.th8=\"Binding Port:\",networkconfightml.form1.addMac=\"Add MAC\",networkconfightml.helper.item1=\"Set the local IP address of the wireless router.\",networkconfightml.helper.item2=\"Set the local subnet mask of the wireless router.\",networkconfightml.helper.item3=\"Sets whether to enable DHCP services enabled for all clients connected to the router automatically assigns IP addresses\",networkconfightml.helper.item4=\"When the DHCP service is enabled, set the auto assigned IP address range.\",networkconfightml.helper.item5=\"When the DHCP service is enabled, set the lease time, non-professionals do not recommend modifying.\",networkconfightml.helper.item6='Reservation is valid only when the DHCP server is enabled, click the \"Add\" button to specify a fixed IP address MAC address binding, this IP address is assigned to only the MAC address belongs to the client.After saving, the rules are automatically added to the IP-MAC binding.',networkconfightml.helper.title1=\"LAN IP\",networkconfightml.helper.title2=\"Subnet Mask\",networkconfightml.helper.title3=\"DHCP Server\",networkconfightml.helper.title4=\"IP Address Pool\",networkconfightml.helper.title5=\"Lease Time\",networkconfightml.ipMacEdit.btn