,DOC.lbl.wanHelps3=\"Wired bridge/mobile hybrid mode DHCP automatic backup function switch, when it is turned on, the system will back up the last DHCP information obtained in bridge mode, so that the next time the system cannot obtain information, it will automatically simulate the upper device to start the server\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkSetting=\"Link detection\",DOC.lbl.adaptiveSwitch=\"Link Detection Switch\",DOC.lbl.adaptiveIntervalTime=\"Adaptive Interval Time\",DOC.lbl.linkDetectionMethod=\"Link Detection Method\",DOC.lbl.tips1=\"Tip: The interval time is 1~1800 s\",DOC.lbl.wanLinktitle1=\"Link detection switch\",DOC.lbl.wanLinktitle2=\"Link detection method\",DOC.lbl.wanLinktitle3=\"IP\",DOC.lbl.wanLinktitle4=\"Detection interval\",DOC.lbl.wanLinktitle5=\"Single mode\",DOC.lbl.wanLinktitle6=\"Mixed mode\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkhelp1=\"Turn on and off the link detection function\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkhelp2=\"Select link detection method\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkhelp3=\"Link detection Server IP address\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkhelp4=\"Link detection interval time, in seconds, the default is 10 seconds\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkhelp5=\"Link detection fixed detection main road\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkhelp6=\"When the response action is not set to restart, the link detection only detects the priority link set by the user; when the response action is set to restart, the link detection detects both the primary link and the backup link\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkTips=\"It is detected that you have not entered any detection IP, whether it is set to the default value, after clicking confirm, the detection IP will be set as follows\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkIP1=\"Detection server IP1\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkIP2=\"Detection server IP2\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkIP3=\"Detection server IP3\",DOC.lbl.wanLinkAction=\"Link Detection Response Action\",DOC.lbl.noAction=\"No Action\",DOC.lbl.actionRestart=\"Restart The Whole Machine\",DOC.lbl.actionWan=\"WAN Automatic Switching\",DOC.lbl.actionDial=\"Re Dial\",DOC.lbl.remindSettings=\"Remind Settings\",DOC.lbl.smsRemindSwitch=\"SMS Remind Switch\",DOC.lbl.phoneRemindSwitch=\"Phone Remind Switch\",DOC.lbl.remindNumber=\"Remind Phone Number\",DOC.lan.gateway=\"Gateway Address\",DOC.lbl.networkStatus=\"Network Status\",DOC.title.wiredWan=\"Wired WAN Information\",DOC.title.wlanWan=\"Wireless WAN information\",DOC.sys.needReboot=\"This operation will restart the device, whether to continue\",DOC.lbl.changeUrl=\"The modification is successful, and you will be redirected to the system status homepage later\",DOC.lbl.flowLimit=\"Warning: Your usage data has exceeded the limit\",DOC.lbl.autoFlush=\"Save successfully, the page will be automatically refreshed later\",DOC.lbl.traffictips1=\"(Range: 0~99999)\",DOC.lbl.traffictips2=\"(Range: 1~\",DOC.lbl.macPageCurrent=\"Current\",DOC.lbl.macPage=\"Page\",DOC.lbl.macPageLast=\"Previous page\",DOC.lbl.macPageNext=\"Next page\",DOC.lbl.macPageSum=\"Total\",CHECK.required.apnname=\"This APN name already exists!\",CHECK.required.apnname2=\"This APN already exists!\",CHECK.tip.lockSpecific=\"In NSA networking mode, the cell lock needs to lock both 4G/5G network standards at the same time\",CHECK.tip.lockBandSUL=\"You can lock the SUL frequency band only after locking at least one common frequency band\",DOC.tr069.linkDMP=\"Unicom DMP\",DOC.tr069.DMPSwitch=\"DMP Switch\",DOC.lbl.DDOSEffect=\"Currently able to defend against both syn-flood and ack-flood attacks.\",DOC.tr069.interval=\"Periodic reporting interval\",DOC.tr069.intervalCycle=\"Period reporting interval value: 30~86400\",TAB.sys.nck=\"NCK Code:\",TAB.sys.functionClose=\"Function is closed\",CHECK.required.nckTimes=\"Remaining input times:\",CHECK.required.locknck=\"NCK code is restricted\",CHECK.required.islocknck=\"Unlocked\",DOC.lbl.addPCI=\"Add PCI\",DOC.lbl.editPCI=\"Edit PCI\",DOC.networkMode.NSA5g=\"5G NSA Only\",DOC.networkMode.SA5g=\"5G SA Only\",DOC.networkMode.net4g=\"4G Only\",MENU.setting.simlock=\"SIM Unlock\",DOC.tzapn.none=\"NONE\",CHECK.format.ipRule=\"IP address is illegal\",CHECK.required.ruleNum=\"The number of rules has reached the upper limit of 32!\",CHECK.required.ruleNum_ipmac=\"The number of rules has reached the upper limit of 20!\",DOC.meshSetting.title=\"Please wait patiently for the system to be configured and try to refresh the page in two minutes...\",DOC.meshSetting.title1=\"Networking switch\",DOC.meshSetting.title2=\"One click networking\",DOC.meshSetting.title3=\"Start networking\",DOC.meshSetting.title4=\"Basic settings\",DOC.meshSetting.title5=\"Networking topology\",wlan5ghtml.helper.title20=\"networking\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item20=\"Prepare at least two CPEs, connect the power supply respectively, and wait for the completion of equipment startup (about two minutes); Connect the WAN port of one CPE to the Internet through the network cable, and the CPE is the main router;\",wlan5ghtml.helper.title21=\"Mode 1 (software mesh networking):\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item21_1=\"1)Log in to the local management page of master CPE and slave CPE respectively, and select 'device configuration' -> “MESH”,Confirm that the networking switch is on, and click the 'start networking' button to wait for networking;\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item21_2=\"2) When the mesh indicator on CPE equipment is always on, it indicates that networking is successful;\",wlan5ghtml.helper.title22=\"Mode 2 (one key networking)\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item22_1=\"1) Log in to the local management page of master CPE and slave CPE respectively, and select 'device configuration'-> “MESH”,Confirm that the networking switch is on;\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item22_2=\"2) Press and hold the WPS / mesh button behind the main CPE for 6 seconds;\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item22_3=\"3) Then, press and hold the WPS / mesh button from the back of CPE;\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item22_4=\"4) Wait for about a minute;\",wlan5ghtml.helper.item22_5=\"5) When the MESH indicator on the router is always on, the networking is successful.\",DOC.sms.selectRead=\"Mark as Read\",DOC.sms.allRead=\"All Read\",DOC.sms.smsTitle=\"SMS\",DOC.sms.rule=\"Cannot send emoticons\",DOC.sms.emptyOutbox=\"No SMS in Outbox\",DOC.table.aclControl=\"Access control\",DOC.table.aclIndex=\"Index\",DOC.table.aclSource=\"Access Source\",DOC.table.aclProtocol=\"Protocol\",DOC.table.aclIPRange=\"IP Address Range\",DOC.table.aclAction=\"Action\",DOC.table.aclStatus=\"Status\",DOC.table.aclOperation=\"Operation\",DOC.table.acltitile=\"Note:\",DOC.table.acltitile1=\"It is recommended that only necessary service be enabled for the LAN\",DOC.lbl.rebootTime=\"Reboot Time\",DOC.lbl.rebootTimeRequire=\"The restart time cannot be empty\",DOC.lbl.rebootTimeRange=\"Reboot time range (3-30) minutes\",DOC.lbl.rebootTimeNeedbiger=\"The restart time cannot be less than the detection interval time\",DOC.lbl.dialTime=\"ReDial Time\",DOC.lbl.dialTimeRequire=\"ReDial Time cannot be empty\",DOC.lbl.dialTimeRange=\"ReDial Time range (10-600) seconds\",DOC.lbl.dialTimeNeedbiger=\"ReDial time cannot be less than the detection interval time\",DOC.lbl.mqttSettings=\"MQTT Settings\",MENU.industry.title=\"Industry Settings\",TAB.industry.serialApplicaiton=\"Serial Applicaiton\",TAB.industry.serialSetting=\"Serial Setting\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.port=\"Serial Port\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.enable=\"enable\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.baudRate=\"baud rate\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.dataBits=\"data bits\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.stopBits=\"stop bits\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.parity=\"parity\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.flowControl=\"flow control\",DOC.industry.serialSetting.getSerialErrorTip=\"Get Serial Infomation Failed,Plese Retry\",DOC.industry.serialDebug.btnText=\"Serial Debug\",DOC.industry.serialDebug.title=\"Serial Data Receive and Send\",DOC.industry.serialDebug.receiveTitle=\"Receive Data\",DOC.industry.serialDebug.receiveFormat=\"Receive Format:\",DOC.industry.serialDebug.stringFormat=\"string\",DOC.industry.serialDebug.hexFormat=\"hex\",DOC.industry.serialDebug.SendTitle=\"Send Data\",DOC